<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-25T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13837: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-25T23:00:00-05:00">December 25, 1936—11
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>90. Your 380, December 25, 7 p.m. If news of Generalissimo Chiang
                            Kai-shek’s release is confirmed and his safety assured, please express
                            appropriately to Foreign Office this Government’s gratification.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>